# Build a Sum and immediately eliminate it with `match`, applying
# different per-lane logic. Each arm runs on its lane's slice;
# `match` reassembles a flat column in original row order.
#
# Heights: short rows are doubled, tall rows are tripled.
# Result: P64[10, 21, 6, 27, 18, 8, 24]

u64[5 7 3 9 6 4 8]
dup 6u64 >=
branch
match {
  -> 2u64 *.u64
  -> 3u64 *.u64
}
